data.title: Jonathan Swift Biography
data.meta_description: Jonathan Swift Biography - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. Jonathan Swift was an Anglo-Irish author and clergyman born in 1667 in Dublin. He is best known for works like Gulliver's Travels and A Modest Proposal which used satire to criticize English politics and customs. After being educated in Ireland and England, Swift worked as secretary to Sir William Temple at Moor Park where he began writing satirical works. He had a career as a political journalist and clergyman in both Ireland and England, using his works to advocate for the Anglican church and criticize the Whig government. In 1713 he became the Dean of St. Patrick's Cathedral in Dublin where he spent much of the rest of his life focused on Irish issues and advocating for Ireland's interests.
